On Sunday, September 25, 2005, at 06:31PM, Mark Hineline <hineline(-at-)ocotillofield.net> wrote:

>Indeed it is. For painting and other tasks (like blowing dust out of 
>the corner) you need an entirely separate hose and a way to bypass the 
>inline oiler.

If the compressor is the piston style and requires oiling, some of the oil slips by the rings and is atomized by the compressor. This must be filtered out of the air for painting. For technicallly clean air, there are various filters you can buy.

